title: Still got it! Misbah-ul-Haq smashes 6 sixes in an over in Hong Kong T20 Blitz – Watch Video - Zee News
text:
News » Sports » Cricket Still got it! Misbah-ul-Haq smashes 6 sixes in 6 balls in Hong Kong T20 Blitz – Watch Video 
The 42-year-old veteran scored 82 from just 37 balls with the help of 7 sixes and 4 fours to guide his team to a total of 216/6. Last Updated: Friday, March 10, 2017 - 09:51 0 Follow @ZeeNewsSports 
New Delhi: Pakistan Test captain, Misbah-ul-Haq, who was retained as the team's skipper for West Indies tour despite several greats including Inzamam-ul-Haq hinting at a change in captaincy, hammered six sixes in six balls for his team Hong Kong Island United in the Hong Kong T20 Blitz on Thursday. 
In the clash against Hung Hom Jaguars, Misbah started the carnage against seamer Imran Arif – smashing him for two sixes in the final two balls of the over – getting the strike back on second delivery in the over of Ashley Caddy – hitting 4 consecutive sixes to complete the feat. All in all, the 42-year-old veteran scored 82 from just 37 balls with the help of 7 sixes and 4 fours to guide his team to a total of 216/6. The opposition, in return, could only managed 183/8. First Published: Friday, March 10, 2017 - 09:45 More from zeenews
